column5: Anyone ever used this braid - they have solid and hollow, gets really great reviews - using 80lbs for musky. Thoughts for Ontario? Any Feedback would be greatly accepted
Haven't used it but looking at it and having trouble understanding their pricing structure.
There's Unicorn hair intertwined, hence the price.
2000yrds for 200 doesn't seem that bad include post to canada - similar to powerpro? Doesn't seem like a unicorn? anyone used this. I have used 832 - my mate brownie swears by this stuff!

I bought their hollow core many years ago from charkbait to try a knotless topshot on  heavy reels. It was good line.   I think they might be done now so anything you see will likely be old stock or discountinued product clearouts.   The company might just be getting another owner, i'm not sure.
